title: Kelly Rohrbach
content:
Kelly Anne Rohrbach[2] (born January 21, 1990) is an American actress and model, best known for her role as C. J. Parker in the film Baywatch.

Was born in New York City and raised in Greenwich, Connecticut.[3] She is the daughter of Anne (née Wholly) and Clay Rohrbach, a financier.[4][5] She attended Greenwich Academy. She played golf for Greenwich and earned an athletic scholarship to Georgetown University to play golf for the Georgetown Hoyas. She graduated from Georgetown in 2012 with a degree in theatre, and enrolled at the London Academy of Music and Dramatic Art to pursue acting.[6]

Rohrbach had small roles in the TV series Two and a Half Men, The New Normal, Rizzoli & Isles, Broad City, and Rush.[6]

After working in Hollywood for two years, Rohrbach began modeling.[7] She appeared in Gap Inc.'s 2014 holiday marketing campaign[6] and for Old Navy denim in 2015.[8] She appeared in the 2015 Sports Illustrated Swimsuit Issue, and was named its "Rookie of the Year".[9] She played C. J. Parker in the 2017 feature film Baywatch, which is based on the 1989–2001 TV series of the same name.[10]

Rohrbach dated actor Leonardo DiCaprio in 2015.[11] In 2019, she married attorney and Walton family heir Steuart Walton.[12] In December 2021, it was announced that the couple were expecting their first child, a boy.[1]
